  <static seed="1205">
    <statement><p>Let <m>f(x) = x^{2}+bx+c\text{.}</m> Let <m>b</m> and <m>c</m> be real numbers. Complete the square to find the vertex of <m>f(x) = x^{2}+bx+c\text{.}</m> Write <m>f(x)</m> in vertex form and then state the vertex.</p>
<p><var form="essay" height="6" width="76"/></p>
</statement>
    <solution><p><me>\begin{aligned}
f(x) = x^{2}+bx+c  \amp = \left(x + \frac{b}{2}\right)^{2} - \frac{b^{2}}{4} +c\\
\amp = \left(x + \frac{b}{2}\right)^{2} - \frac{b^{2}}{4} +\frac{4c}{4}\\
\amp = \left(x + \frac{b}{2}\right)^{2} + \frac{4c-b^{2}}{4}
\end{aligned}</me></p>
<p>Thus, the vertex is <m>(\frac{-b}{2},\frac{4c-b^{2}}{4})\text{.}</m></p>
</solution>
